tr.td: Title: Cardiology Office Visit Note New

1. Anemia (D64.9: Anemia, unspecified)
With anemia unable to take Eliquis because of recurrent GI bleeding will send the patient to electrophysiology for placement of watchman device. Continue the present medication for now patient will be seen in 3 months for reevaluation
2. Chronic kidney disease, stage 3b, GFR 33, Creatinine 1.84 Labs 2023-02-28 (N18.32: Chronic kidney disease, stage 3b)
3. Atrial flutter (I48.92: Unspecified atrial flutter)
Patient with history of atrial flutter.
4. Hernia, umbilical (K42.9: Umbilical hernia without obstruction or gangrene)
5. Chronic renal insufficiency (N18.9: Chronic kidney disease, unspecified)
Chronic renal insufficiency hold have the patient continue follow-up with nephrology Dr.Tres Palacios.
6. Renal insufficiency (N28.9: Disorder of kidney and ureter, unspecified)
Chronic renal insufficiency will follow-up with nephrology as outpatient as well.

Patient is here for hospital follow up.
